Customer Lifetime Profit


This page is a sensitivities calculator that shows the behaviour of the core business model. It models a single customer with a fractional churn.

The editable parameters on this page DO NOT affect the main business model.

Churn is the no of customers who drop off each month
CAC is the Customer Aquisition Cost (Marketing Cost) of a new customer
COGS is the Cost Of Goods Sold (server rental costs)
Price is the price per month
CC Fee is the percentage of the Price that is paid in Credit Card Fees
")

Customer Lifetime Profit


This page is a sensitivities calculator that shows the behaviour of the core business model. It models a single customer with a fractional churn.

The editable parameters on this page DO NOT affect the main business model.

Churn is the no of customers who drop off each month
CAC is the Customer Aquisition Cost (Marketing Cost) of a new customer
COGS is the Cost Of Goods Sold (server rental costs)
Price is the price per month
CC Fee is the percentage of the Price that is paid in Credit Card Fees
